  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Inclusive Emergency Response for Men and Women affected by floods in Sofala Province</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will predominantly target older women and men (60+), including older people with disabilities and their care givers. The small RNA-OP highlighted this groups specific vulnerabilities. In Sofala Province 90% of older women and men do not have enough food, with 70% going to bed hungry. 42% depend on family and friends to meet their basic needs and 30% of older people living alone are not able to reach the services alone. The response will therefore focus on protection and inclusion to ensure food security, health, WASH and shelter activities are accessible for older people and older people with disabilities. Ensuring access for OP and OP with disabilities to life-saving services in their community is essential in providing full protection for this high-risk community.</narrative>
  </description>
